 What methods does GeminiAgent implement beyond the required interface?\\n4. Are there any methods on CopilotAgent that aren't needed by the interface or used externally?\\n\\nFocus on finding the minimal set of methods/types the copilot agent actually needs.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"938245c2-7917-44a5-941b-1f244ef62062\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T02:49:33.251Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Compare the copilot package (cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/) with the gemini package (cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/) to identify:\\n\\n1. What methods does the Agent interface require? Read cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go and cmd/entire/cli/agent/types.go to find the interface definition\\n2. What methods does CopilotAgent implement beyond the required interface?\\n3. What methods does GeminiAgent implement beyond the required interface?\\n4. Are there any methods on CopilotAgent that aren't needed by the interface or used externally?\\n\\nFocus on finding the minimal set of methods/types the copilot agent actually needs.\",\"agentId\":\"a31a550\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KqfpdcYBkriiFBUKoHrLwr\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01X2FNBxzbgUN6Z1dTRjvBmr\",\"uuid\":\"8e1cb104-c04f-42bb-afce-09c6d58f07c2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T02:49:33.251Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8e1cb104-c04f-42bb-afce-09c6d58f07c2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"80f8a4c6-43a7-40f7-ae13-62f0cc2727dc\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/github-copilot-support\",\"slug\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015pkBF3afQfp9zFzbMPr55c\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→package copilot\\n     2→\\n     3→import \\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n     4→\\n     5→// HookConfig represents the .github/hooks/copilot-setup.json structure\\n     6→type HookConfig struct {\\n     7→\\tVersion int                    `json:\\\"version\\\"`\\n     8→\\tHooks   map[string][]HookEntry `json:\\\"hooks\\\"`\\n     9→}\\n    10→\\n    11→// HookEntry represents a single hook command entry\\n    12→type HookEntry struct {\\n    13→\\tType       string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    14→\\tBash       string `json:\\\"bash\\\"`\\n    15→\\tTimeoutSec int    `json:\\\"timeoutSec,omitempty\\\"`\\n    16→}\\n    17→\\n    18→// --- Hook stdin types (from actual Copilot CLI v0.0.411 capture) ---\\n    19→//\\n    20→// Common fields: only \\\"timestamp\\\" (unix milliseconds) and \\\"cwd\\\" are present in all hooks.\\n    21→// \\\"sessionId\\\" and \\\"transcriptPath\\\" are only present in the agentStop hook.\\n    22→\\n    23→// hookBase contains the only fields present in ALL Copilot hook stdin JSON.\\n    24→type hookBase struct {\\n    25→\\tTimestamp int64  `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n    26→\\tCwd       string `json:\\\"cwd\\\"`\\n    27→}\\n    28→\\n    29→// sessionStartRaw is the stdin JSON for the sessionStart hook.\\n    30→// Example: {\\\"timestamp\\\":1771465283476,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"initialPrompt\\\":\\\"...\\\"}\\n    31→type sessionStartRaw struct {\\n    32→\\thookBase\\n    33→\\n    34→\\tSource        string `json:\\\"source,omitempty\\\"`\\n    35→\\tInitialPrompt string `json:\\\"initialPrompt,omitempty\\\"`\\n    36→}\\n    37→\\n    38→// sessionEndRaw is the stdin JSON for the sessionEnd hook.\\n    39→// Example: {\\\"timestamp\\\":1771465290000,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"complete\\\"}\\n    40→type sessionEndRaw struct {\\n    41→\\thookBase\\n    42→\\n    43→\\tReason string `json:\\\"reason,omitempty\\\"`\\n    44→}\\n    45→\\n    46→// userPromptRaw is the stdin JSON for the userPromptSubmitted hook.\\n    47→// Example: {\\\"timestamp\\\":1771465282293,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"prompt\\\":\\\"...\\\"}\\n    48→type userPromptRaw struct {\\n    49→\\thookBa